name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: dfs.storage.policy.satisfier.max.outstanding.paths
description:
Defines the maximum number of paths to satisfy that can be queued up in the
    Satisfier call queue in a period of time. Default value is 10000.

name: nfs.server.port
description: Specify the port number used by Hadoop NFS.

name: mapreduce.job.running.map.limit
description:
The maximum number of simultaneous map tasks per job.
  There is no limit if this value is 0 or negative.

name: nfs.mountd.port
description: Specify the port number used by Hadoop mount daemon.

name: dfs.bytes-per-checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  dfs.stream-buffer-size
